rows.title: Harry Potter Multicross CYOA Mod
rows.titleText: Congratulations on your acceptance to Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry. You have been reincarnated into a muggle child and have gained magic which has let you be accepted into Hogwarts. You have also gained magical abilities as well as ghostly figures who can follow you around and teach you about your magic.

objects.title: Target
objects.text: Who is going through the CYOA?

objects.title: Difficulty
objects.text: How many points do you start with? Has no bearing on the rest of the CYOA.

objects.title: Powers
objects.text: Choose the magical abilities and systems that you have access to.

objects.title: House
objects.text: Choose the Hogwarts House you are sorted into.

objects.title: Time
objects.text: Choose the time period you insert into.

objects.title: Drawbacks
objects.text: Choose drawbacks that can help you gain more powers.

objects.title: You
objects.text: You are the one going through the CYOA. All the choices here affect you.

objects.title: Someone Else
objects.text: Someone else you know is going through the CYOA. All the choices here affect them.

objects.title: Meta
objects.text: You are the one going through the CYOA-after you go through another CYOA. Make a build with some other CYOA first.

objects.title: Easy
Mistborn (Mistborn Trilogy)
objects.text: You receive the powers of a full mistborn. Your ghostly mentor is Kelsier.

objects.title: Magus (Nasuverse)
objects.text: You receive thirteen average quality magic circuits. Your ghostly mentor is Lord El-Melloi II.

objects.title: Parahuman (Worm)
objects.text: You recieve a copy of Myrrdin's power. Your ghostly mentor is Eidolon.

objects.title: Practitioner (Pact)
objects.text: You are a freshly awakened Practitioner. Your ghostly mentor is Rose Thorburn.

objects.title: Sorcerer (Dark Souls)
objects.text: You have Sorcerous abilities. Your ghostly mentor is Big Hat Logan.

objects.title: Dot Mage (Zero no Tsukaima)
objects.text: You are a dot mage. Your ghostly mentor is Karin of the Heavy Wind.

objects.title: Wizard? (Harry Potter)
objects.text: You don't gain any extra abilities, just Albus Dumbledore's talent with magic. Your ghostly mentor is Severus Snape, as of his death.

objects.title: Aura (RWBY)
objects.text: You receive Aura equivalent to that of the average student at Signal Academy. Your ghostly mentor is Adam Taurus.

objects.title: Name (Practical Guide to Evil)
objects.text: You are a claimant to a Name which is based off of your circumstances and disposition. Your ghostly mentor is the Black Knight, Amadeus of the Green Stretch.

objects.title: Force-Sensitive (Star Wars)
objects.text: You are a Force-Sensitive with a midi-chlorian count of 10,000. Your ghostly mentor is Jolee Bindo.

objects.title: Chakra (Naruto)
objects.text: You have a Chakra Capacity equivalent to that of the average Genin at the Konohagakure Academy. Your ghostly mentor is Anko Mitarashi.

objects.title: Psyker (Warhammer 40K)
objects.text: You are an Epsilon-Class Psyker. Your ghostly mentor is Jaq Draco.

objects.title: Gryffindor
objects.text: The Sorting Hat chooses students possessing characteristics such as courage, chivalry, nerve and determination for Gryffindor.

objects.title: Slytherin
objects.text: The Sorting Hat chooses students possessing characteristics such as cunning, resourcefulness, leadership, and ambition for Slytherin.

objects.title: Hufflepuff
objects.text: The Sorting Hat chooses students possessing characteristics such as hard work, dedication, patience, loyalty, and fair play for Hufflepuff.

objects.title: Ravenclaw
objects.text: The Sorting Hat chooses students possessing characteristics such as wit, learning, and wisdom for Ravenclaw.

objects.title: Philosopher's Stone
objects.text: Your first year of Hogwarts is the same as Harry Potter's.

objects.title: Order of the Phoenix.
objects.text: Your first year of Hogwarts is the year that the Dolores Umbridge teaches at Hogwarts.

objects.title: War Era
objects.text: You insert some time during Harry Potter's Parents stay at Hogwarts.

objects.title: Fantastic Beasts
objects.text: You insert some time around when Fantastic Beasts is taking place.

objects.title: Deepness (Mistborn)
objects.text: Heavy mists have begun to appear near magical sites, and they swirl around people who use magic. Strange fleshy creatures haunt these mists. The mists will eventually end up attacking sixteen percent of the nearby population and awakening Allomantic abilities in them.

objects.title: Escape
objects.text: The Dementors have left Azkaban and begun to attack people randomly. All the prisoners of Azkaban have escaped.

objects.title: Abyss (Pact)
objects.text: Lost and forgotten areas have begun to disappear into the Abyss, and Bogeymen are sent after you to bring you under the Abyss's hold.

objects.title: Grigori (Dragon's Dogma)
objects.text: A massive dragon has appeared and will attack various areas in search for someone with sufficient willpower to become a being known as the Arisen. The dragon will rip out the Arisen's heart, and it can only be killed by the Arisen who will have to kill the dragon to regain it.

objects.title: Grail War (Nasuverse)
objects.text: Fourteen people have gained red markings on their hand. An Apocrypha Grail War has begun, with the two major factions being the sides. The grail will simply support the war and will not grant wishes.

objects.title: Highstorm (The Stormlight Archive)
objects.text: Powerful storms have begun to periodically rage in a select few areas. They will leave behind a type of magical energy known as Stormlight.

objects.title: Dispersal (Charlotte)
objects.text: A comet has just passed by the Earth, spreading dust all throughout. A small percentage of pre-adolescent children who inhale the dust will manifest superhuman abilities upon reaching puberty.

objects.title: Grimm (RWBY)
objects.text: Pools of a strange dark liquid have begun to form in a select few places. Grimm will rise from these pools and target locations with negative emotions to wreak havoc.

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
